data.name: Classic Apple Crisp
data.quickTastyDescription: A warm, comforting dessert featuring tender apples topped with a crunchy oat and brown sugar crumble.
detailedCookingInstructions: In a large bowl, mix the sliced apples with 1/2 cup of brown sugar, cinnamon, nutmeg, and salt until well combined. Spread the apple mixture evenly in a 9x13 inch baking dish.
In another bowl, combine the oats, flour, remaining brown sugar, and melted butter. Mix until crumbly and combined.
Spread the oat mixture over the apples in the baking dish.
Bake in the preheated oven for 35-45 minutes, or until the apples are tender and the topping is golden brown.
Allow to cool slightly before serving.
data.modifiersForBase: Add vanilla ice cream for a la mode option.
